Title: Safe Query Languages for Constraint Databases  
Author: Peter Z. Revesz 
Keyword: Categories and Subject Descriptors: H.2.3 [Database Management]: Languages|Query Languages; H.2.1 [Database Management]: Logical Design|data models General Terms: Database, Languages Additional Key Words and Phrases: Constraint databases, datalog, relational calculus, safety  
Affiliation: University of Nebraska-Lincoln  
Abstract: In the database framework of [Kanellakis et al. 1990] it was argued that constraint query languages should take as input constraint databases and give as output other constraint databases that use the same type of atomic constraints. This closed-form requirement has been difficult to realize in constraint query languages that contain the negation symbol. This paper describes a general approach to restricting constraint query languages with negation to safe subsets that contain only programs that are evaluable in closed-form on any valid constraint database input. 
